  "title": "Tender Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>In charge of maintaining trackers, schedules, and approval logs to ensure timely and error-free submissions.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in compiling tender submissions, integrating inputs from factories</li>\n  <li>Taking charge following and executing the assigned task within the timelines</li>\n  <li>Responsible in supporting internal approval workflows by preparing required documents ahead of deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Responsible in ensuring version control, formatting consistency, and compliance of all submissions with internal standards.</li>\n  <li>In charge of document clarification responses, track progress for ongoing tenders, organize follow-up actions and escalate, where necessary.</li>\n  <li>Request and track vendor quotations; compile comparative summaries for review.</li>\n  <li>Manage document version control and implement quality checks for accuracy and compliance.</li>\n  <li>Support handover of secured opportunities to project teams with complete documentation packages for tender closure and transitions</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Diploma in Engineering/ Project Management or relevant</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience in tendering, engineering, or project support</li>\n  <li>Experience in Transmission &amp; Distribution and/or Power Systems is required</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online<strong> </strong><a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com</strong></a><strong> </strong>or call <strong>+(65)</strong> <a href=\"tel:6232 7810\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a><strong> </strong>for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
